    <span>READ TIME: 3 min</span>
    <span>CATEGORY: Inventory</span>
  </div>

  <h2>// The Stocky Shutdown — What's Happening</h2>
  <p>
    Shopify announced that Stocky, its built-in inventory management app, will be shut down in August 2026. Stocky has been available free for Shopify merchants since 2019 when Shopify acquired the original app. It was one of the few inventory tools that did not carry a monthly subscription fee, which made it the default choice for small-to-mid-size Shopify stores managing purchase orders and supplier relationships.
  </p>
  <p>
    The shutdown affects all Stocky users regardless of plan level. Shopify has not announced a built-in replacement — instead pointing merchants toward the third-party app ecosystem. This creates a genuine problem: the direct equivalents in the Shopify App Store cost $49–$299/month for functionality that was previously free.
  </p>

  <h2>// Free vs Paid Replacements</h2>
  <p>
    Your choice depends on how complex your inventory operations are. For most merchants who used Stocky for purchase orders and supplier tracking, the free route covers everything needed.
  </p>

