    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>// What Stocky Features Does Stocky Swap Cover?</h2>
  <p>
    Stocky's core functionality covers four areas: creating and sending purchase orders to suppliers, managing supplier contacts and lead times, viewing demand forecasts based on sales velocity, and generating suggested orders when stock runs low. Stocky Swap replicates all four without requiring an app install or paid subscription.
  </p>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <div class="label">MIGRATION NOTE</div>
    <p style="margin:0; font-size:13px;">Most merchants complete the Stocky to Stocky Swap migration in under 30 minutes. Export your supplier list from Stocky (Settings → Export), import it into Stocky Swap, and verify your open purchase orders. Historical purchase order data can be exported as CSV before Stocky shuts down in August 2026.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>// When to Choose a Paid Alternative</h2>
  <p>
    Stocky Swap is the right answer for the majority of Shopify merchants. A paid alternative makes sense if you need: real-time multi-channel inventory sync across Amazon, eBay, and Shopify simultaneously; warehouse bin location management and pick-pack-ship workflows; barcode scanning for receiving and stock counts; or EDI integration with large retail partners. These are enterprise use cases — if you were on Stocky, you almost certainly do not need them.
  </p>

